.<br><br>The killer is in a car accident and taken to a hospital. During tests, like MRI and Scans, the storm does a mean job on the electricity and everything goes berserk. He happens to die at that same time. Well, he is able to enter the computer and survive there.<br><br>A couple of pages of Karen Allen's address book had been copied as a demonstration by another employee earlier at the PC store to show her a new program. That's where she forgot her book.<br><br>In life, the address book killer used real life address books, but now he had access to the pages from the address book in the computer in order to hunt down and kill friends of Karen Allen's.<br><br>It's really a great flick if you like that sort of thing ... and I do. How does the killer in the computer kill his victims? He is able to affect all kinds of electric appliances and other electrically run machines at businesses. Some of the scenes are pretty gross ... Just remember ... It's all special effects.<br><br>I recommend it highly. Very enjoyable. <br><br>~~~Dottie~~~ <p><img src=http://photoasa.com/disk1/708/19781_DottieHM.gif><br>"The love for all living creatures is the noblest attribute of man."<br>~~~Charles Darwin~~~<br>Please visit us at the <font size=3><a href="http://pub12.ezboard.com/bthoughtmessageboard">Thought Message Board</a><br>Guardian 507<br><font size=1><a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/btheguardianacademy">The Guardian Academy</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/umercrising2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>merc rising2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BatWoman</span><br>  Posts: 991<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/13/01 6:38:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=titl